Definition.WordDefinition: Backwoods \Back"woods"\, n. pl. [Back, a. + woods.] The forests or partly cleared grounds on the frontiers. [1913 Webster]
backwoods adj : inaccessible and sparsely populated [syn: {backwoods(a)}, {outback(a)}, {remote}] n : a remote and undeveloped area [syn: {back country}, {boondocks}, {hinterland}]
